<item>
            <title>[CXF-1924] Infinite loop in FileUtils.getDefaultTempDir() when &quot;java.io.tmpdir&quot; directory does not exist</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-1924</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;FileUtils.getDefaultTempDir() can go into a infinite loop when the &quot;java.io.tmpdir&quot; system property is set to an non-existent directory. Here&apos;s the code that causes the problem:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            s = System.getProperty(&quot;java.io.tmpdir&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
            File f = new File(s, &quot;cxf-tmp-&quot; + x);&lt;br/&gt;
            while (!f.mkdir()) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                x = (int)(Math.random() * 1000000);
                f = new File(s, &quot;cxf-tmp-&quot; + x);
            }
</description>
