                            <comment id="12653846" author="seanoc" created="Fri, 5 Dec 2008 16:03:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;added check to code and a unit test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12969844" author="eric.citaire" created="Thu, 9 Dec 2010 18:25:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to reopen this issue because it still goes in an infinite loop when the property is set to an non-&lt;b&gt;writable&lt;/b&gt; directory. The fix doesn&apos;t check that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;May be something like this would prevent an infinite loop :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;s = System.getProperty(&quot;java.io.tmpdir&quot;);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;File checkExists = new File(s);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;if (!checkExists.exists() || !checkExists.isDirectory() || !checkExists.canWrite()) {&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;tt&gt;throw new RuntimeException(&quot;The directory &quot;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;tt&gt;+ checkExists.getAbsolutePath()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;tt&gt;+ &quot; is not a writable directory&quot;);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;}&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;File f = new File(s, &quot;cxf-tmp-&quot; + x);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;for (int attempts=0; attempts&amp;lt;10; attempts++) {&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;tt&gt;x = (int)(Math.random() * 1000000);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;tt&gt;f = new File(s, &quot;cxf-tmp-&quot; + x);&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &lt;tt&gt;if (f.mkdir()) break;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;}&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
